<p>Connect to the specified FTP server. </p>
<p>The port has a default value of 21, which is the standard port used by the FTP protocol. You shouldn't use a different value, unless you really know what you do. This function tries to connect to the server so it may take a while to complete, especially if the server is not reachable. To avoid blocking your application for too long, you can use a timeout. The default value, <a class="el" href="classsf_1_1Time.php#a8db127b632fa8da21550e7282af11fa0" title="Predefined &quot;zero&quot; time value.">Time::Zero</a>, means that the system timeout will be used (which is usually pretty long).</p>
